Burning,\" British Lion |url=https://eu.sctimes.com/story/entertainment/2020/01/22/local-cd-pick-the-burning-british-lion/4523344002/ |website=sctimes.com |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Monkhouse |first1=Paul |title=Album Review : British Lion \u2013 \u2018The Burning |url=https://metalplanetmusic.com/2020/01/gig-review-british-lion-the-burning/ |website=Metal Planet Music |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Popoff |first1=Martin |title=BRITISH LION \u2013 \u201cIT\u2019S EMOTIONAL AND IT\u2019S POWERFUL AND IT\u2019S REAL\u201d |url=http://bravewords.com/features/british-lion-its-emotional-and-its-powerful-and-its-real |website=BraveWords |accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Johnson |first1=Kevin |title=Steve Harris and British Lion Release \u201cThe Burning\u201d |url=https://www.notreble.com/buzz/2020/01/22/steve-harris-and-british-lion-release-the-burning/ |website=No Treble |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref> It was released January 17, 2020, and was produced by Harris itself. It was the first album under only moniker British Lion, transforming the project from solo to band.\n\nThe album was preceded by the singles \"Spit Fire\" on October 26, 2018, \"Lightning\" on October 31, 2019, and the title track \"The Burning\" on December 13, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=IRON MAIDEN Bassist's BRITISH LION: Watch Music Video For 'The Burning' Title Track |url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/iron-maiden-bassists-british-lion-watch-music-video-for-the-burning-title-track/ |website=Blabbermouth.net |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kielty |first1=Martin |title=Listen to Steve Harris\u2019 New British Lion Song \u2018The Burning\u2019  Read More: Listen to Steve Harris\u2019 New British Lion Song \u2018The Burning\u2019 |url=https://ultimateclassicrock.com/british-lion-the-burning/ |website=ultimateclassicrock.com |accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Colothan |first1=Scott |title=Exclusive: British Lion premiere 'The Burning' video |url=https://planetradio.co.uk/planet-rock/news/rock-news/british-lion-the-burning-video/|website=planetradio.co.uk |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Graff |first1=Gary |title=Steve Harris Shares Title Track to British Lion's 'The Burning': Premiere |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8545910/british-lion-the-burning-steve-harris |website=Billboard |accessdate=November 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the release of '''''The Burning''''', critics published reviews on their thoughts of the album. '''Metal Planet Music''' voiced that \"the first thing that strikes you is the music, great hard rock with melody and class, but it\u2019s the heart and emotion that will stay with you long after the last note rings out. Coming eight years after their debut, \u2018'''''The Burning'''''\u2019 is the second album by '''British Lion''' and the [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] led quintet have made a record that is at once modern, nostalgic and timeless\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metalplanetmusic.com/2020/01/gig-review-british-lion-the-burning/|title=Album Review : British Lion \u2013 \u2018The Burning|last=Authoradmin|date=2020-01-22|website=Metal Planet Music|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs are written by Richard Taylor, David Hawkins and [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]], except where noted.\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = \n| headline        =\n| total_length    = 60:11\n| title1          = City of Fallen Angels\n| length1         = 5:20\n| writer1         = \n\n| title2          = The Burning\n| length2         = 5:15\n| writer2         = \n\n| title3          = Father Lucifer\n| length3         = 4:38\n| writer3         = \n\n| title4          = Elysium\n| length4         = 5:11\n| writer4         =\n\n| title5          = Lightning\n| length5         = 5:49\n| writer5         = \n\n| title6          =